==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dipyre
<hw>Di*pyre"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>di-</grk> =
<grk>di`s-</grk> twice fire.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of
the scapolite group; -- so called from the double effect of fire upon
it, in fusing it, and rendering it phosphorescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dipyrenous</ent>⟦br⟧
